PRE RUN:
Front-end:
Install android studio
install flutter and set up the emulator at version 9 API-28 (https://flutter.dev/docs/get-started/install)

in terminal of the IDE, run:
flutter pub add cloud_firestore
flutter pub add http
flutter pub add modal_progress_hud_nsn
flutter pub add flutter_speed_dial
flutter pub add flutter_barcode_scanner

packages dependencies:
cupertino_icons: ^1.0.2
cloud_firestore: ^2.2.0
http: ^0.13.3
modal_progress_hud_nsn: ^0.1.0-nullsafety-1
flutter_speed_dial: ^3.0.5
flutter_barcode_scanner: ^2.0.0


To open the emulator go to the AVD manager. Then hit run in the IDE to open the app in the emulator.


Back-end:
Make sure you've installed python3 (version 3.7 or above)
pip3 install torch
pip3 install google-cloud-storage
pip3 install firebase
pip3 install firebase_admin
pip3 install flask
pip3 install flask_restful
pip3 install ortools
pip install numpy
pip install pandas
pip install matplotlib
pip install tabulate

HOW TO RUN:

set FLASK_APP=app.py
python3 app.py
